++ SYNOPSiS                                                                  +ª
ª+---------------------------------------------------------------------------+ª
At the piano bar Kaoru encounters Fujii who looks exactly identical to Makabe, 
her dead lover and fiance. Fujii happens to be Tatsuro's superior at work; he 
had just transferred from Kansai to his new position. Naoto witnesses the 
conversational intimacy of Kaoru and Fujii, and begins to wonder. When the concert 
is finished, a little girl hands Kaoru a bouquet of flowers. She's Mika, Fujii's 
daughter. Fujii invites Kaoru to have dinner with them, and Mika wants to take 
piano lessons from her. Naoto goes to see Tatsuro at his workplace, to warn him that 
ôKaoru is seeing another man ... [who] looks like Makabe-san.ö Tatsuro refuses to 
believe him but decides to ask Kaoru about it anyway ...

